      <div id=3D"divSymbol" class=3D"Entry">
         <h2>Chord Symbol</h2>
         <div class=3D"p">
            <div class=3D"p">
               Enter the symbol you'd like to analyze. You can use lowercas=
e b and # as substitutes
               for the =E2=99=AD and =E2=99=AF characters. You can use lowe=
rcase o, =C2=B0, or <i>dim</i>
               to indicate diminished chords. You can use =C3=B8, <i>hd</i>=
, or minor seven
               =E2=99=AD5 notation to indicate half diminished chords. You =
can use lowercase m, -, or
               <i>min</i> for minor. To indicate major sevenths, you can us=
e uppercase M,
               <i>maj</i>, or =E2=96=B3. To indicate augmented chords, use =
+ or <i>aug</i>.
            </div>
            <div class=3D"p">
               Chord&nbsp;Calculator is liberal in what it accepts, but con=
servative in its reply.
               However you enter a chord, it'll be rewritten using your sta=
ted chord symbol
               preferences. Also, it may optimize or rearrange the chord sy=
mbol you've entered. For
               example,
               G<span class=3D"lp">(</span>add4<span class=3D"Mis Cap">omit=
</span>3<span class=3D"rp">)</span>
               is accepted, but G<span class=3D"lp">(</span>sus4<span class=
=3D"rp">)</span> is returned.
               Also, some input may be ambiguous. For example, G4 might mea=
n
               G<span class=3D"lp">(</span>add4<span class=3D"rp">)</span> =
or
               G<span class=3D"lp">(</span>sus4<span class=3D"rp">)</span>,=
 but Chord&nbsp;Calculator
               will always assume a suspended chord is intended. Another po=
ssible area of ambiguity is
               an accidental that appears between the root and a numeral. I=
n this case,
               Chord&nbsp;Calculator will always apply the accidental to th=
e root note. For example,
               F=E2=99=AF11 will be interpreted as an F=E2=99=AF chord with=
 extensions through the
               eleventh, not an F chord with a sharp 11th. To make the dist=
inction, use parentheses.
            </div>
            <div class=3D"p">
               The constituent notes of the chord will be displayed.
            </div>
         </div>
         <input type=3D"text" maxlength=3D"35" id=3D"txtSymbol" autocomplet=
e=3D"off" autocapitalize=3D"off" spellcheck=3D"false">
      </div>

